■ Neo Evolution: You may put it on one of your Jokers. (If a creature is under it, treat it as a Neo Evolution Creature.)
{DOUBLE BREAKER}
■ Whenever this creature attacks, you may discard 2 Jokers from your hand. If you do, untap this creature.

{NEO EVOLUTION}: You may put it on one of your Darkness creatures. (If a creature is under it, treat it as a Neo Evolution Creature.)
{TRIPLE BREAKER}
■ At the end of each of your turns, if this creature is tapped, you may put a non-evolution creature that costs 8 or less from your graveyard into the battle zone.

{NEO EVOLUTION}: You may put it on one of your Nature creatures. (If a creature is under it, treat it as a Neo Evolution Creature.)
{TRIPLE BREAKER}
■ Whenever this creature attacks, you may put a non-evolution nature creature that has power 12000 or more from your hand into the battle zone.

{TRIPLE BREAKER}
■ When you put this creature into the battle zone, reveal the top 3 cards of your deck. Put all creatures that have power 12000 or more from among them into your hand, then put the rest on the bottom of your deck in any order.
■ When this creature would be discarded by one of your opponent's spell effect or creature ability, you may put it into the battle zone instead.
